abstract: IN the history of opera in New York, 1966 is a landmark year. That was the season when, on Sept. 16, the Metropolitan Opera  inaugurated its new house at Lincoln Center with a Murphy's Law production of Samuel Barber's "Antony and Cleopatra."

abstract: PORTLAND, Ore., Nov. 2--A heady wave of euphoria, probably based more on exhaustion than political reality, has engulfed the Anderson for President campaign just before the election.

abstract: CHICAGO, Nov. 1--In key industrial and undecided states, such as Illinois, the broadcasting of material dealing with politics begins at dawn and ends after midnight in the final electronic assault of the 1980 campaigns--state, local and Presidential. Here is a log of the impressions left by a day in front of a television set.
headline_main: Soap Operas and Politics Are Strange Bedfellows

abstract: TOKYO, Nov. 2 (AP)--The 12-member United States women's golf team beat Japan by 19 strokes and captured the team title for the second straight year today in the $100,000 Japan-United States Pioneer Cup women's professional golf tournament.
headline_main: U.S. Women Golfers Win Title in Japan
headline_print_headline: U.S. Women Golfers Win Title in Japan

abstract: Mr. and Mrs. Stanley Merves of Haverford, Pa., have announced the engagement of Mrs. Merves's daughter, Amy Hope Lubart, to Richard Kain Breslow, son of Dr. and Mrs. Irwin Breslow of Philadelphia. A July wedding is planned.

abstract: Mr. and Mrs. Nathaniel H. Hurwitz of Great Neck, L.I., have announced the engagement of their daughter, Amy Louise Hurwitz, to Louis A. Gordon, son of Mrs. Nash Gordon of New York and the late Mr. Gordon. A December wedding is planned.
